# Shile, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Shile (; ) is a rural locality (a selo) in Kuzhniksky Selsoviet, Tabasaransky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. As of the 2010 census, its population was 207 people, with 269 people in the 2002 census and 218 in the 1989 census. There are 3 streets.
Geography
Shile is located 15&nbsp;km west of Khuchni (the district's administrative centre) by road. Kharag is the nearest rural locality.
